    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-06-30T16:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-06-30T16:00:00-05:00" n="701"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d701">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">860H.00/6–3048: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Douglas</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret   urgent</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-06-30T22:00:00+01:00"
                            >June 30, 1948—10 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2905. For the Secretary and Lovett from Douglas. Bevin<note n="1"
                        xml:id="d701fn1">Ernest Bevin, British Secretary of State for Foreign
                        Affairs.</note> today told me that he had received word from Belgrade that
                    US was considering, against the background of the <gloss target="#t_Cominform1"
                        >Cominform</gloss> action in regard to Yugoslavia, issuing a statement
                    announcing our support for small countries.</p>
                <p>Bevin suggests that we refrain from issuing any such statement until there has
                    been an appreciation of the <gloss target="#t_Cominform1">Cominform</gloss>
                    action and to have a clearer view of its considerations and significance.<note
                        n="2" xml:id="d701fn2">Telegram 2505, July 1, to London, not printed,
                        replied in part as follows: “Please assure Bevin Dept shares his view
                        desirability withholding statement re Yugo developments pending further
                        clarification and evaluation and has already instructed Emb Belgrade that
                        sense.” (860H.00/6–3048)</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Douglas</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
